{
  "video_id": "_CFJ1u-DIBc",
  "title": "Why Does Bluetooth Still Suck?",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 0.0,
      "end_time": 1870.0,
      "text": "Has this ever happened to you?"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 2720.0,
      "end_time": 4100.0,
      "text": "You're not alone."
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 4100.0,
      "end_time": 5989.0,
      "text": "Apple, Google and other companies"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 5990.0,
      "end_time": 9380.0,
      "text": "have gotten rid of the headphone jack from their phones."
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 9380.0,
      "end_time": 12610.0,
      "text": "This is pushing people towards wireless headphones,"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 12610.0,
      "end_time": 14170.0,
      "text": "which means they'll have to rely"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 14170.0,
      "end_time": 15930.0,
      "text": "on that Bluetooth connection."
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 15930.0,
      "end_time": 18240.0,
      "text": "The Bluetooth is still so unreliable."
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 18240.0,
      "end_time": 21549.0,
      "text": "Its got a short range, devices disconnect randomly"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 21550.0,
      "end_time": 23540.0,
      "text": "and it uses up battery life."
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 23540.0,
      "end_time": 26310.0,
      "text": "Even thought it's been around for 20 years, why does Bluetooth still suck?"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 28730.0,
      "end_time": 32770.0,
      "text": "Bluetooth is a wireless standard used all around the world."
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 32770.0,
      "end_time": 35550.0,
      "text": "Wireless printers, keyboards, game controllers,"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 35550.0,
      "end_time": 38669.0,
      "text": "speakers and headphones all use it."
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 38670.0,
      "end_time": 41330.0,
      "text": "It was created by a group of engineers in the mid '90's"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 41330.0,
      "end_time": 44870.0,
      "text": "as a secure way to exchange data between devices,"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 44870.0,
      "end_time": 46900.0,
      "text": "the Bluetooth name and logo come from"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 46900.0,
      "end_time": 50230.0,
      "text": "10th century viking king Harald Gormsson who,"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 50230.0,
      "end_time": 51900.0,
      "text": "similar to Bluetooth's purpose,"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 51901.0,
      "end_time": 56901.0,
      "text": "unified two separate entities, Denmark and Norway."
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 57300.0,
      "end_time": 59410.0,
      "text": "King Harald's nickname was Blatand,"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 59410.0,
      "end_time": 62419.0,
      "text": "which translates from Danish to Bluetooth."
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 62420.0,
      "end_time": 66260.0,
      "text": "The logo comes from the initials of King Harald Blatand."
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 66270.0,
      "end_time": 69740.0,
      "text": "It is a combination of the runic letters H and B."
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 69747.0,
      "end_time": 73620.0,
      "text": "Bluetooth uses the 2.4 gigahertz frequency"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 73620.0,
      "end_time": 75690.0,
      "text": "to communicate with other devices."
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 75690.0,
      "end_time": 78380.0,
      "text": "This frequency and a few others are referred to"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 78380.0,
      "end_time": 81509.0,
      "text": "as the ISM band, for Industrial„ÄÅ"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 81510.0,
      "end_time": 83960.0,
      "text": "Scientific and Medical devices."
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 83960.0,
      "end_time": 86890.0,
      "text": "This is the spectrum that baby monitors"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 86900.0,
      "end_time": 88340.0,
      "text": "and cordless phones all use."
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 88340.0,
      "end_time": 89680.0,
      "text": "It's also the same frequency,"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 89680.0,
      "end_time": 92420.0,
      "text": "fluorescent lights and microwaves omit."
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 92420.0,
      "end_time": 94670.0,
      "text": "These frequencies don't require devices"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 94670.0,
      "end_time": 97460.0,
      "text": "to have an FCC license to operate on them."
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 97460.0,
      "end_time": 100229.0,
      "text": "This makes the band attractive to manufacturers"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 100230.0,
      "end_time": 102410.0,
      "text": "because they don't have to deal with the FCC."
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 102410.0,
      "end_time": 105348.0,
      "text": "Because of this, the ISM is brimming with devices."
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 105349.0,
      "end_time": 108550.0,
      "text": "And they all interfere with your Bluetooth devices."
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 108550.0,
      "end_time": 110429.0,
      "text": "Any device running on Bluetooth,"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 110430.0,
      "end_time": 112970.0,
      "text": "falls into one of three classes."
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 112970.0,
      "end_time": 116640.0,
      "text": "Class one, for long range, these need a power supply,"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 116640.0,
      "end_time": 119690.0,
      "text": "and are mainly used for industrial purposes."
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 119690.0,
      "end_time": 122370.0,
      "text": "They have a range of nearly 330 feet."
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 122370.0,
      "end_time": 125680.0,
      "text": "Class two, they have a range of about 30 feet."
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 125680.0,
      "end_time": 128550.0,
      "text": "This is what most cellphones and speakers use."
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 128550.00000000001,
      "end_time": 131890.0,
      "text": "Class three devices have a range of less than 30 feet."
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 131890.0,
      "end_time": 133489.0,
      "text": "Class two and three devices"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 133490.0,
      "end_time": 135689.0,
      "text": "generally use low power Bluetooth."
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 135689.0,
      "end_time": 137650.0,
      "text": "But even low power can use"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 137650.0,
      "end_time": 140120.0,
      "text": "a precious battery life on your phone."
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 140120.0,
      "end_time": 141800.0,
      "text": "And if you have a class two speaker,"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 141800.0,
      "end_time": 143800.0,
      "text": "20 feet away from your phone,"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 143800.0,
      "end_time": 145710.0,
      "text": "it still may not work great."
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 145710.0,
      "end_time": 147540.0,
      "text": "Especially if there's any interference"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 147540.0,
      "end_time": 149160.0,
      "text": "coming from other devices."
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 149160.0,
      "end_time": 153116.0,
      "text": "Bluetooth also transfers data much slower than WiFi does."
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 153116.0,
      "end_time": 156980.0,
      "text": "While devices connected via the new WiFi Direct standard"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 156980.0,
      "end_time": 160540.0,
      "text": "will be able to transfer data at 250 megabits per second,"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 160540.0,
      "end_time": 162530.0,
      "text": "Bluetooth 4.0 can only get up"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 162530.0,
      "end_time": 165470.0,
      "text": "to 25 megabits per second max."
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 165470.0,
      "end_time": 168740.0,
      "text": "There's no superfix for these issues coming anytime soon."
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 168740.0,
      "end_time": 170450.0,
      "text": "But if you want to improve the connection"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 170450.0,
      "end_time": 173750.0,
      "text": "between two devices, there are a few things you can do."
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 173750.0,
      "end_time": 176800.0,
      "text": "Keep the devices as close together as possible."
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 176800.0,
      "end_time": 178460.0,
      "text": "Keep your devices updated."
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 179430.0,
      "end_time": 181270.0,
      "text": "Reset your connections daily."
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 183330.0,
      "end_time": 186790.0,
      "text": "Or even use a device that can amplify a Bluetooth signal."
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 186790.0,
      "end_time": 188403.0,
      "text": "While there's no sure fix yet,"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 188403.0,
      "end_time": 191530.0,
      "text": "some companies are taking matters into their own hands,"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 191530.0,
      "end_time": 194660.0,
      "text": "developing technology that works a lot like Bluetooth."
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 194660.0,
      "end_time": 197570.0,
      "text": "Apple's W1 chip enables its AirPods"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 197570.0,
      "end_time": 199680.0,
      "text": "to switch to whatever device you're using,"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 199681.0,
      "end_time": 202510.0,
      "text": "rather than having to unpair and re-pair"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 202510.0,
      "end_time": 204399.0,
      "text": "the devices each time."
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 204400.0,
      "end_time": 206120.0,
      "text": "Will we start seeing other companies"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 206130.0,
      "end_time": 208600.0,
      "text": "take wireless communication into their hands?"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 208611.0,
      "end_time": 210683.0,
      "text": "We'll just have to wait and see."
    }
  ]
}